&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/details&gt;

 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/validate-stack-sequences/&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given two integer arrays  &lt;code&gt;pushed&lt;/code&gt;  and  &lt;code&gt;popped&lt;/code&gt;  each with distinct values, return &lt;em&gt; &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt;  if this could have been the result of a sequence of push and pop operations on an initially empty stack, or  &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt;  otherwise&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; pushed = [1,2,3,4,5], popped = [4,5,3,2,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; true&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; We might do the following sequence:&lt;br /&gt;
push(1), push(2), push(3), push(4),&lt;br /&gt;
pop() -&amp;gt; 4,&lt;br /&gt;
push(5),&lt;br /&gt;
pop() -&amp;gt; 5, pop() -&amp;gt; 3, pop() -&amp;gt; 2, pop() -&amp;gt; 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; pushed = [1,2,3,4,5], popped = [4,3,5,1,2]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; false&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 cannot be popped before 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;解題思路&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#解題思路&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 解題思路&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;solution&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#solution&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
